Rhodium trifluoride is the inorganic compound with the formula RhF3.  It is a red-brown, diamagnetic solid.  


== Synthesis and structure ==
The compound is prepared by fluorination of rhodium trichloride:

2 RhCl3 +  3 F2  â†’   2 RhF3  +  3 Cl2According to X-ray crystallography, the compound adopts the same structure as vanadium trifluoride, wherein the metal achieves octahedral coordination geometry.


